        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:42PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 542 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stapleton, or 7 miles north of Loxley, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Daphne, Spanish Fort, Loxley, and Stapleton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
